### User Management Tests
### Test CRUD operations cho users với Role-based Authorization

# ==========================================
# SETUP: Get tokens for different roles
# ==========================================
@gatewayUrl = http://localhost:3000
### Login as Admin
# @name loginAdmin
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@test.com",
  "password": "Admin@123456"
}

### Login as Customer
# @name loginCustomer
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "customer@test.com",
  "password": "Customer@123456"
}

###

@adminToken = {{loginAdmin.response.body.accessToken}}
@customerToken = {{loginCustomer.response.body.accessToken}}

# ==========================================
# AUTHORIZATION TESTS
# ==========================================

### 1. List All Users (Admin only - should pass)
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/users?page=1&pageSize=10
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 1b. List All Users as Customer (should fail with 403)
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/users?page=1&pageSize=10
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

###

### 1c. List All Users without token (should fail with 401)
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/users?page=1&pageSize=10

### 2. Search Users by Name/Email (Admin only)
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/users?search=nguyen&page=1&pageSize=10
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 3. Get User by ID (Both Admin and Customer allowed)
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/users/user-123
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

###

### 3b. Get User by ID as Admin
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/users/user-123
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 4. Get User by Email (Admin only)
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/users/email/customer@test.com
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 4b. Get User by Email as Customer (should fail with 403)
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/users/email/customer@test.com
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

### 5. Update User Info (Both Admin and Customer allowed)
PUT {{gatewayUrl}}/users/user-123
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName": "Updated Name",
  "phone": "0123456789"
}

###

### 6. Deactivate User Account (Admin only)
PUT {{gatewayUrl}}/users/user-456/deactivate
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### 6b. Deactivate as Customer (should fail with 403)
PUT {{gatewayUrl}}/users/user-456/deactivate
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

###

# ==========================================
# AUTHENTICATION TESTS
# ==========================================

### 7. Try to access without token (expect 401)
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/users

###

### 8. Try with invalid token (expect 401)
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/users
Authorization: Bearer invalid.token.here

###

### 9. Try with expired token (expect 401)
# You would need to use an actual expired token here
# GET {{gatewayUrl}}/users
# Authorization: Bearer expired.token

# ==========================================
# AUTHORIZATION ERROR EXAMPLES
# ==========================================

### 10. Customer tries to access admin-only endpoint (expect 403 with detailed message)
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/users
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

###

### 11. Test role-based error message format
# The response should include:
# {
#   "statusCode": 403,
#   "message": "Access denied. Required roles: ADMIN. Your role: CUSTOMER",
#   "error": "Forbidden"
# }
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/users/email/admin@test.com
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}